      • registerModule

        protected DarwinServer.ModuleRegistration registerModule(java.lang.Class<?> module,
                                                         java.lang.String source)
        Register a given module and create a singleton instance of it.

        If a module carries the DisabledModule annotation the module will not be loaded. This is to be defined by the creator of the module if the module is unstable or not ready for production.

        If a module is Deprecated there will still be an attempt to register and instantiate it, however a different DarwinServer.ModuleRegistration state is returned.

        Parameters:
        module - The module to register
        source - the source
        Returns:
        The resulting state of the registration
